name: More Section
description:
For some of the test cases in this section, you must have access to the MLB App Tools - QA. The changes done at the client cannot be proxied since the call is signed by the HTTP client at the origin. So, to test these, you must login to the tool and make the changes manually and then verify the changes in the app. Once you made your changes in the tool, publish them to QA and give it a minute for the system to update. Then relaunch the app and the changes should be reflecting in the app.
Check out this short video on how to test with the config changes: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MBbUxPMVmSJPFUjyr2ucRXme2p_lsdnf/view?usp=sharing

name: N/A - Ask MLB - Question Bot
description:
IAB-15657

As a user I would like to be able to ask At Bat to answer specific baseball stats queries such as:
Who led the league in ERA in 1975?
Who is the all time AL Steals Leader?
Who holds the single season record for On Base percentage?

The user should press a microphone button which would open up a sheet with a "capturing indicator" like Siri (a waveform animation indicating that it is listening)
As the user speaks, we would show text to translation
The answer would be provided with a link to the correct view in Stats to get a deeper answer
Error handling would be provided if it doesn't understand the query

https://wiki.mlbam.com/pages/viewpage.action?spaceKey=mobile&title=At+Bat+-+Question+Bot+-+Phase+1

description:
Design https://www.figma.com/design/5nJ9AKwH8HqlLq7pSRoKnh/Apple-Watch-Specs?node-id=158-31351&t=5IHhlpKWRDs22geb-0

Game states: 

Delayed start - game hasn't started and has a new start time. Will be played on the same day
Delayed - game started and is delayed but will finish on the same day
Postponed - games hasn't started but has to be rescheduled on another day
Suspended - game started but has to be finished on another day. Game will have a resumed state
